    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. but if the \"success\" of the intervention basically led to a massive power vacuum, civil war, and a huge increase in regional instability and human trafficking, doesn't that kind of negate the initial success? it feels like the long-term geopolitical cost was way higher than the short-term gain of just removing one guy.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
