    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't know, it feels like you're splitting hairs there. if a doctor performs a successful surgery but the patient dies a week later because the doctor didn't plan for the recovery, was the surgery actually a \"success\"? isn't it a bit of a stretch to call it a geopolitical success when the entire region became a mess because of it? it seems like the intervention and the post-intervention phase are totally inseparable in real-world politics.",
