      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In real-world geopolitics, the long-term outcome is the only metric that truly matters, making the intervention an overall failure. A successful military action that precipitates regional anarchy and human suffering cannot be deemed a success by any reasonable standard. The failure to plan for the aftermath demonstrates a fundamental strategic incompetence that negates any short-term tactical victory. Therefore, the entire operation must be judged as a catastrophic geopolitical blunder.",
      "source": "target",
